rComments: Took her class during the Summer of 2018 and I must say she is a wonderful professor overall! Very knowledgeable and she is always willing to help any questions you may have. I would recommend her class to anyone at UofT. Her tests are based solely on lecture material (which is a plus bc I basically ignored the textbook and got a high A).
Very interesting lectures, still remember her lessons over two years later. She has a deep knowledge of her subject and is an excellent teacher.

No papers ! Tests are based on lecture materials ( she co-authored the textbook, so lectures and textbooks are basically say the same thing ). You don't really have to memorize the researchers' name ( though she said so) they just serve as retrieval cues on the tests. Overall, great prof !
EASY. GREAT PROF. GREAT LECTURES. MUST TAKE.

Took her class in Fall 2012 (finally getting around to rating it).She was very organized & clear--since she co-wrote the textbook,there was no disparity b/t her lectures & the book.I learned a ton!I like that she emphasized learning psychs' names;it's a good habit to adopt early on in your studies. Hint:final exam is detailed.Read the book closely!
